{{Other people|James Adams}} '''James W. Adams''' of [[Southville, Kentucky]] was a carpenter, builder, and designer in south central [[Shelby County, Kentucky]].<ref name=mra>{{NRHP url|id=64000253|title=Shelby County MRA}}</ref>
A number of his works are listed on the U.S. [[National Register of Historic Places]].<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref>
